Do you want to know the BIG difference between a success story and those who stay stuck? 
 
Here's the thing, sometimes when you want more out of life it can feel like a struggle and everything can feel overwhelming... 
 
Marketing seems too hard, support from your family doesn’t exist, your friends think your crazy, the money isn’t there, you see others crushing it and wonder when it'll be your time… 
 
First, I want you to know you aren't alone! 
 
Second thing, most of the time those thoughts are just a delusion because those obstacles are only a part of your story... they're not YOUR whole story. 
 
Over the years, I haven’t met one successful person that hasn’t had those same stories and struggles... those same fears and insecurities. 
 
The big difference between a success story and those who didn’t go for it? 
 
RESOURCEFULNESS. 
 
They found a way even when they didn’t have resources. 
Even when people told them they were crazy. 
Even when it looked like it wouldn't work... 
 
They became more RESOURCEFUL. 
 
They used what they had, they learned from their mistakes and gained knowledge from others... 
 
And today, right NOW you have access to so many resources that some of the world's most successful people never had! Google, YouTube, podcasts, books, courses, masterminds... 
 
It's time to stop looking for obstacles and start looking for OPPORTUNITIES. 
 
You have everything you need right now to write YOUR SUCCESS STORY... 
 
Because listen, life is going to happen no matter what... whether you go for it or not. 
 
Don't you want to look back and say I went for it? 
 
Don't you want to say I played full out and left nothing on the table? 
 
Become resourceful and write your SUCCESS story. 
 
How can you become more resourceful today? 👇 
 
🔥 P.S. Want access to a bunch of resources? Check out the Mastermind.com membership. Right now you can take it for a test drive for 14 days for just $1 and we're donating that dollar to charity. Get a rolling start on success in 2023. 👆
 
#resourcefulness #successhabits #entrepreneurinspiration #entrepreneurmindset #successmindset #goafteryourdreams #goalsetting

Listen, I know life gets busy and it's easy to let things fall by the wayside. You get caught up in the hustle and bustle of every day life... 
 
And now with the holidays things can get even busier with family, kids on vacation, maybe you're traveling or getting ready to host and that's why now more than ever it's important to make sure the people you love most know how much you love and appreciate them... 
 
It's like my dear friend Tony Robbins says "Energy flows where attention goes." 
 
These last few months have been incredibly busy with launches, events... a newborn! And I feel so blessed to have my amazing wife @lisafresa by my side. 
 
I love this woman deeper than I knew I was able to love and I have to tell you that we truly do fall more in love every single day and its because we both put our focus and attention into our relationship. 
 
We go on date nights and I still leave her love notes and send her flowers and she takes care of me and our family so well... somedays it feels like she's doing everything for me. Haha. 
 
She loves doing things for me and I love doing things for her. We work on our love everyday because it’s important to us... 
 
Lisa, you are the love of my life and I thank God for you every day. ♥️ Thank you for loving me the way you do. 
 
If you're in a relationship, I want to encourage you to step up the love in your relationship for the next 30 days. Make sure your significant other knows how much you love and appreciate them and watch your relationship strengthen and grow. 
 
If you're not in a relationship, I hope this post inspires you to see what's possible. Listen... I had to become a better man to attract this amazing woman. So put your focus and attention on becoming a better YOU to attract the love you want. 
 
Comment 🙌 if you're committed to putting more focus and attention into your relationships this month.

Are you overcomplicating gratitude? 👇 
 
You know how important gratitude is right? It's one of the biggest contributors to your happiness and overall well-being...  
 
But I think sometimes when we practice gratitude we can set the bar so high we're looking for some BIG, magical thing that happened...  
 
And when you really start to make gratitude a HABIT you start to realize there are so many things, SO MANY things to be grateful for.  
 
Like you've heard me say before the little things ARE the big things.  
 
So today, I want to challenge you to KEEP IT SIMPLE when it comes to gratitude because there is so much to be grateful for if you're open to seeing it. 
 
You have to make it a PRACTICE... a habit to train your mind to start looking for all that's right instead of focusing on what's wrong.  
 
Here's 3 things I’m grateful for today… 
1. Waking up everyday next to the love of my life @lisafresa 
2. Spending time with my amazing kids 
3. This incredible community  
 
Ok! I want to hear from you. Drop in the comments, what are 3 things you're grateful for? 👇

On Valentine's Day we get to be grateful for the one we love, the one who makes our heart race, the one who makes us work so hard... the one who puts next level purpose in our lives. 
 
This Valentine's Day I'd like to say all those things to my amazing wife @lisafresa, but it transcends that, beyond just today... when it's love for the long-term. 
 
And if you're not there yet, you get to dream about what IS possible because it is possible and keep reading because I believe this is an important message for everyone to understand about what REAL LOVE is... 
 
Right now we have two teenagers, we have a soon-to-be three year old son, who has eczema and 8 allergies that are life-threatening and we have a 3-month old daughter who we just found out has the same exact issues... 
 
I'm busier than I've ever been running two companies and obsessed with impacting other people's lives. Lisa has her own business, but she's put that on hold to take care of our children because of these serious health conditions to make sure they're safe and taken care of. 
 
Now, I'm not saying any of this like "poor me," in fact quite the opposite... 
 
It's in times like these when you get to practice the real muscle of LOVE, the real muscle of CONNECTION, the real muscle of LONGEVITY.. 
 
Love isn't measured when everything is perfect and the roses smell fresh and the wine is crisp and it's the 4th date without responsibility. 
 
REAL LOVE is measured when it's taxed, when it's pushed, when it's stressed, when it's not perfect.... 
 
And at the end of the day, I know how deep my love is for my wife Lisa because with all we have going on I look at her and I know why I'm on this Earth. 
 
Happy Valentine's Day to everyone, whatever it means to you... 
 
What it means to me is I have my ride for life. No matter what's going on with the outside world... no matter how tough it is, I love her and I have her back. 
 
She's my muse. 
She's my everything. 
She's the love of my life. 
 
I love you Lisa, Happy Valentine’s Day ♥️

Last night I found out that my friend Dave Hollis passed away at 47 years old…  today would have been his birthday. 💔 
 
It’s hard to find the words or articulate feelings when it feels so unfair... 
 
But I can say, though the time was too short, I’m grateful for the time I got to know Dave as a friend and the time we spent together just recently. 
 
I loved watching him stretch himself to become the man he knew he was designed to be. 
 
He made such an incredible impact on so many... and if you ever got to watch him with his children. you couldn't help but smile. You could see and feel how much he loved them. 
 
During this difficult time, I ask that you please pray for his children and his family. 🙏🏼❤️ 
 
And while this is incredibly sad and does seem so unfair, let's remember to love today and everyday in honor of our friend Dave. 
 
@mrdavehollis, you will surely be missed my friend, the world seems a little less bright today.

Every night I wrestle 🤼 with my 3-year old Luca on the bed... that's a fact. 
 
No matter how hard my day is, no matter how busy I am, no matter how stressed I am... taking this time to play with Luca is a PRIORITY to me because with my oldest child being 16 I see how fast the time goes. 
 
Well last week while wrestling with Luca... he usually climbs up the back and jumps down into the pillow... I didn't realize he was jumping and I moved the pillow to see where he was and BOOM 💥 the top of his head came crashing into my eye. 
 
Now, is there ever a "good time" for a black eye? I don't think so, haha... but talk about inconvenient! 
 
I was in the middle of doing multiple live events with tens of thousands of people and I'm in the middle of filming a course and I get this crazy black eye because I was wrestling with my 3-year old... 
 
Not so much fun and I looked horrific but in the big picture... who cares? 
 
At the end of my life, I'm not going to look back and say I wish I would've been able to film without a black eye that week. 
 
I'll look back and remember that's the week I was wrestling with my 3-year old every night (and Luca will have a great story too haha)... 
 
👉 Remember what's important. 
 
Schedule it. 
Do it. 
 
And keep showing how up no matter what. 💪

⛰️ What “mountain” do you need to climb this week? 

I used to hike Camelback Mountain 3 days a week for about 5 years…

And I obsessively I used to time myself. 

I had gotten down to 24 minutes! 💪

Then with the pandemic they closed down the trail and I never came back. 

I see this mountain everyday. I drive by it everyday…

but I’ve been INTIMIDATED by it because I knew I wouldn’t be close to my old time hiking it. 

I didn’t want to see how 🫣 bad my time was because it was important to me. 

Well, a few weeks ago I hiked it again for the first time in years with my son…

Guess how long it took? 

40 minutes! 

It took us 40 minutes to get to the top. Then I did it again a few days later… 39 minutes. 

WAY OFF from where I used to be. 

And my brain 🧠 wants to tell me to QUIT, don’t do it, that I’ll never get my old time back…

But I’ve TRAINED myself, I’ve trained my brain to say “No! I must do it. I must climb.” 

Now I have to do it 3 days a week. I have to get back to my old time… 

even though I don’t want to. 

So let me ask you… 👉 what’s the tough thing you’re putting off that you need to tackle? 

What’s the thing that’s intimidating you because you’re AFRAID you won’t be good enough or it might be tough at first? 

Don’t think about how hard it is to start… focus on the OUTCOME. 

Focus how you’ll feel 🙌 when you accomplish it. 

Then GO DO IT. 

So what’s your “mountain?” Share with me in the comments and let’s cheer each other on. 👇
